channel.title: No where else to turn
channel.description:
This is my last hope for help. I have tried RuneL0cus Rune-Server, Syth3, everywhere, for days.
PLEASE IF YOU NO HOW TO HELP ME... HELP ME.
Heres the problem;
I coded a decent server, although I ran the client through "localhost" so I didn't know if other people could connect to it, I just assumed they could, because I mean, who the hell makes a server thats like hard-coded to localhost? WTF? Anyway, I'm not sure if its hard-coded or not, but when you change the IP, it changes for you, but other players cant log in. It says "Error connecting to server" for them. YES, I portforwared, set my variables, opened my firewall on my router set up, I've done everything. Even Runel0cus says its online..... I can run other servers, because I've coded a previous project. This is seriously pissing me off because I've worked hard on it.
If you can help me VIA TeamViewer or what ever, please.
If you'd like more Information, heres what I got:
ORIGINAL THREAD: http://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php/topic,397390.msg2950299.html#msg2950299
I know this is probably the wrong section, and I'm sorry but no one pays attention to that section.

Do you even know what the hell “hard-coded” means?

Yes. Do you know what leeching is? Yes you do, all your servers are leeched.

Hard-coded means that you will code something directly into the RuneScape cache. Not overlapping it.

And I’m pretty sure my servers are not “leeched”.

No shit. Anyway, they are. You can’t release a new “project” every week and expect it to be the best of your ability’s. Either you dont sleep, or you leech.
[/quote]

His servers are actually pretty good, and hey, aren’t you the idiot that is asking us how to CONNECT TO A SERVER? :|[/quote]

For one, I released a project a while ago using conventions that would top everything you could ever do, so yeah. And I’m just now coming BACK to RSPS, I’ve worked with PHP and HTML In class’s and haven’t had time for Java/C++. It was a simple question, if your to ignorant to answer it don’t post. Its that simple, if you dont know what your doing, leave.

And… I’m not fimilar with all these new models and crappy shit in clients nowadays, so EXCUSE ME.
